more%20companies%20boost%20production%2C%20manufacturing%20sophisticated%20weaponry%20simply%20is%20not%20quick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20Laliberty%2C%20Raytheon's%20president%20of%20land%20and%20air%20defense%20systems%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fus-patriot-defeat-europe-sampt-air-defense-volodymyr-zelenskyy%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CIt%2520takes%2520us%252012%2520months%2Cof%2520rapidly%2520ramping%2520up%2520production.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20Politico%20last%20year%20that%20it%20takes%2012%20months%20to%20build%20a%20Patriot%20radar%2C%20just%20one%20part%20of%20an%20operational%20battery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESophistication%20is%20a%20key%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBronk%20said%20missiles%20designed%20to%20attack%20are%20easier%20to%20build%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20much%2C%20much%20cheaper%20to%20build%20offensive%20missiles%20than%20it%20is%20to%20build%20defensive%20interceptor%20coverage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20price%20reflects%20that%20sophistication%3A%20Naval%20interceptors%2C%20like%20the%20SM-series%2C%20can%20cost%20up%20to%20almost%20%2430%20million%20a%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223702%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20interceptor%20missile%20being%20launched%20from%20a%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20at%20sea.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66326ef210dfcda40965690c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222468%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20SM-3%20Block%201B%20interceptor%20missile%20is%20launched%20from%20the%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Lake%20Erie.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDefense%20systems%20are%20%26quot%3Bsome%20of%20the%20most%20sophisticated%20bits%20of%20hardware%20that%20militaries%20have%2C%20and%20producing%20them%20takes%20time%20with%20pretty%20skilled%20labor%2C%26quot%3B%20former%20Australian%20Army%20Maj.%20Gen.%20Mick%20Ryan%2C%20a%20warfare%20strategist%2C%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasing%20production%20enough%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20a%20challenge%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c60e8a9-0ab9-4eb7-945c-7f73b5c4a485%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20steps%20forward%2C%20but%20challenges%20remain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20alliance%20is%20taking%20steps%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetired%20Air%20Commodore%20Andrew%20Curtis%2C%20an%20airfare%20expert%20with%20a%2035-year%20career%20in%20the%20Royal%20Air%20Force%2C%20said%20countries%20speaking%20confidently%20gives%20the%20industry%20the%20reassurance%20it%20wants%20to%20invest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGovernments%20are%20now%20talking%20the%20right%20language%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20industry%20saw%20investing%20in%20production%20facilities%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20sound%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20demand%20was%20there.%20But%20that%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20industry%20would%20not%20invest%20long-term%20in%20expensive%20facilities%20that%20require%20skilled%20workers%20%26quot%3Bwith%20no%20guaranteed%20orders%20at%20the%20end%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreased%20cooperation%20is%20also%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20has%20cultural%20problems%2C%20with%20countries%20working%20separately.%20Jan%20Kallberg%2C%20a%20security%20expert%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20European%20Policy%20Analysis%2C%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20major%20challenge%20in%20NATO%20is%20not%20money%2C%20it's%20coordination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20companies%20working%20on%20similar%20systems%20means%20doubling%20up%20on%20some%20expenses%2C%20and%20makes%20scaling%20up%20harder%2C%20Kallberg%20said.%20Fixing%20that%20%26quot%3Bwould%20free%20up%20a%20tremendous%20lot%20of%20resources.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilitary%20officials%20want%20greater%20collaboration.%20A%20US%20general%20last%20month%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdefense-firms-quit-selling-pieces-puzzle-work-together-us-general-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurged%20defense%20firms%20to%20coordinate%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20%26quot%3Bstop%20selling%20us%20pieces%20of%20the%20puzzle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProgress%20is%20happening%3A%20More%20companies%20and%20countries%20are%20working%20together.%20The%20Nordic%20countries%20are%20integrating%20their%20air%20defenses%20to%20act%20as%20one%2C%20and%20with%20joint%20air%20defense%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20are%20taking%20place%20at%20the%20top%20level.%20The%20European%20Commission%20is%20proposing%20new%20measures%20to%20cut%20red%20tape%2C%20encourage%20joint%20purchases%2C%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20facilitate%20billions%20of%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20challenges%20remain.%20Kallberg%20warned%3A%20%26quot%3BCulture%20takes%20far%20more%20time%20to%20change%20than%20just%20buying%20hardware.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-promise-air-defense-spending-money-alone-wont-solve-issue-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751793782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6867aad33d5881a51c1cb9d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-promise-air-defense-spending-money-alone-wont-solve-issue-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22NATO%20promised%20to%20use%20members'%20soaring%20defense%20budgets%20for%20a%20fivefold%20increase%20in%20air%20defenses.%20But%20there%20are%20problems%20beyond%20spending%20to%20fix.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbaker%40insider.com%20(Sin%C3%A9ad%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-promise-air-defense-spending-money-alone-wont-solve-issue-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22It's%20illegal%20in%20most%20states%20for%20private%20equity%20to%20buy%20a%20law%20firm.%20Lawyers%20have%20figured%20out%20a%20workaround.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20statue%20of%20Justice%20inside%20of%20a%20loop%20hole%20being%20painted%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6862eb1785e81483682d12b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELegal%20ethics%20rules%20generally%20don't%20allow%20non-lawyers%20to%20own%20law%20firms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMSOs%20are%20a%20workaround%20to%20allow%20nonlawyers%2C%20including%20private%20equity%20firms%2C%20to%20effectively%20invest.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELaw%20firm%20owners%20can%20use%20the%20investors%20to%20scale%2C%20as%20well%20as%20for%20succession%20planning.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EReal%20estate%2C%20airlines%2C%20fashion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20seem%20like%20private%20equity%20has%20climbed%20the%20mountain%20of%20the%20American%20economy%2C%20declaring%20everywhere%20the%20light%20touches%20as%20part%20of%20its%20kingdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20corner%20remains%20in%20the%20shadowlands%3A%20Law%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20every%20state%20has%20adopted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanbar.org%2Fgroups%2Fprofessional_responsibility%2Fpublications%2Fmodel_rules_of_professional_conduct%2Frule_5_4_professional_independence_of_a_lawyer%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessional%20ethics%20rule%20from%20the%20American%20Bar%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20forbidding%20lawyers%20from%20working%20for%20nonlawyer-owned%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%2C%20of%20course%2C%20have%20figured%20out%20a%20way%20around%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20loophole%2C%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmanaged%20services%20organization%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20or%20MSO%20%E2%80%94%20allows%20non-lawyers%20to%20effectively%20own%20part%20of%20law%20firms%20through%20a%20second%20corporate%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20two%20attorneys%20who%20advise%20law%20firms%20on%20the%20arrangement%2C%20which%20they%20said%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bloomberglaw.com%2Flegal-ops-and-tech%2Ftax-friendly-puerto-rico-approves-non-lawyer-owners-of-law-firms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPuerto%20Rico's%20high%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20allowed%20non-lawyer%20investment%20in%20law%20firms%20in%20order%20to%20spur%20economic%20development%20in%20the%20territory.%20Arizona%2C%20the%20only%20state%20that%20has%20done%20away%20with%20the%20ABA%20rule%2C%20in%202020%2C%20now%20has%20over%20100%20law%20firms%20that%20are%20open%20to%20outside%20investors%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flaw.stanford.edu%2Fpublications%2Flegal-innovation-after-reform-five-years-of-data-on-regulatory-change-3%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20Stanford%20Law%20School%20study%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Large%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkpmg-law-firm-big-four-us-legal-services-market-arizona-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKPMG%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Rocket%20Lawyer%20now%20own%20law%20firms%20in%20the%20state%20outright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MSO%20model%2C%20which%20isn't%20limited%20to%20only%20Arizona%2C%20could%20appeal%20to%20law%20firm%20owners%20who%20want%20to%20retire%20or%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20hand%20their%20firms%20over%20to%20a%20law%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20largest%20rolling%20retirement%20of%20lawyers%20in%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lucian%20Pera%2C%20a%20legal%20ethics%20attorney%20at%20Adams%20%26amp%3B%20Reese%20who%20advises%20lawyers%20and%20businesses%20about%20setting%20up%20MSOs.%20%26quot%3BThe%20baby%20boomers%20are%20getting%20old%20and%20retiring.%20And%20that's%20a%20real%20opportunity%20for%20some%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20an%20MSO%20can%20give%20private%20equity%20firms%20%E2%80%94%20or%20other%20kinds%20of%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20a%20chance%20to%20effectively%20buy%20a%20slice%20of%20legal%20practices.%20And%20it%20gives%20lawyers%20the%20chance%20to%20sell%20stakes%20of%20their%20companies%20for%20cold%2C%20hard%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20also%20offer%20the%20chance%20to%20partner%20with%20a%20deep-pocketed%20company%20that%20could%20boost%20the%20firm%20and%20help%20scale%20it%20to%20new%20heights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ced28a4-0c3b-4cd8-ba3e-f2599728ec17%5C%22%3ENo%20one%20says%20MSOs%20are%20not%20OK%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20law%20firms%20have%20operated%20as%20partnerships%20among%20attorneys%2C%20where%20equity%20partners%20own%20shares%20in%20the%20firm%20and%20help%20manage%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20partly%20because%20of%20ethics%20rules%20designed%20to%20maintain%20attorney%20independence%2C%20such%20as%20ABA%20Model%20Rule%205.4(d)%2C%20which%20largely%20prevents%20nonlawyers%20from%20owning%20law%20firms%20or%20from%20having%20the%20right%20to%20control%20the%20professional%20judgment%20of%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ABA's%20rules%20have%20made%20law%20practices%20distinct%20from%20many%20other%20white-collar%20professions%2C%20like%20finance%20or%20consulting%2C%20which%20may%20have%20robust%20ethical%20rules%20and%20norms%20but%20don't%20impose%20such%20stringent%20limits%20on%20ownership.%20There%20are%20plenty%20of%20publicly%20traded%20banks%20and%20consulting%20firms%2C%20but%20no%20publicly%20traded%20law%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20workaround%2C%20the%20law%20firms%20can%20set%20themselves%20up%20as%20two%20corporate%20entities%2C%20Pera%20said.%20One%20is%20the%20law%20firm%20itself%2C%20composed%20exclusively%20of%20lawyers%20and%20owned%20only%20by%20lawyers.%20The%20second%20is%20the%20service%20organization%2C%20which%20can%20be%20owned%20by%20anyone%20and%20acts%20as%20a%20vendor%20for%20the%20law%20firm.%20It%20is%20essentially%20the%20back%20office%2C%20taking%20care%20of%20all%20non-lawyer%20tasks%2C%20including%20marketing%2C%20accounting%2C%20human%20resources%2C%20real%20estate%20leases%2C%20and%20employing%20paralegals.%20The%20two%20corporate%20entities%20enter%20into%20a%20long-term%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20this%20MSO%20arrangement%2C%20non-lawyers%20can%20invest%20in%20the%20service%20corporation%2C%20though%20not%20the%20law%20firm%20itself.%20Presto!%20You%20have%20an%20ethically%20independent%20group%20of%20lawyers%20who%20are%20exclusively%20working%20with%20a%20company%20that%20can%20sell%20shares%2C%20Pera%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Pera%2C%20no%20state%20bars%20have%20issued%20ethics%20opinions%20that%20expressly%20bless%20the%20MSO%20model%2C%20but%20no%20court%20or%20regulator%20has%20found%20a%20problem%20with%20it%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pieces%20fit%20well%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20regulatory%20approval%20required%20for%20a%20law%20firm%20to%20do%20it%2C%20just%20like%20there's%20no%20regulatory%20approval%20required%20for%20a%20law%20firm%20to%20take%20out%20a%20bank%20loan%2C%26quot%3B%20Pera%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20American%20Bar%20Association%20said%20its%20Center%20for%20Professional%20Responsibility%20doesn't%20have%20any%20ethics%20opinions%20on%20non-lawyers%20investing%20in%20MSOs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLawyers%20are%20not%20subject%20to%20the%20ABA%20Model%20Rules%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20they%20are%20regulated%20by%20the%20state%20supreme%20courts%20in%20which%20they%20are%20licensed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224e71cbd3-e068-4381-bf57-3913d68f63c6%5C%22%3EOpportunities%20for%20both%20lawyers%20and%20investors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETom%20Lenfestey%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20The%20Law%20Market%20Exchange%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20Craigslist%20for%20law%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20private%20equity%20companies%20are%20typically%20interested%20in%20consumer-driven%20firms%2C%20like%20personal%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20might%20be%20able%20to%20introduce%20new%20efficiencies%20into%20those%20firms%20and%20get%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20revenue%20in%20a%20larger%20portfolio%2C%20said%20Lenfestey%2C%20who%20also%20advises%20on%20law%20firm%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20equity%20companies%20might%20be%20warier%20of%20investing%20in%20Big%20Law%20firms%2C%20which%20typically%20service%20corporations%20and%20have%20fewer%20but%20bigger%20clients%2C%20he%20said.%20Lawyers%20could%20always%20jump%20ship%20and%20take%20clients%20with%20them%2C%20but%20consumer%20law%20firms%20tend%20to%20do%20steadier%20business%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPersonal%20injury%20is%20brand-marketed%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20billboards%2C%20it's%20the%20TV%2C%20it's%20the%20digital%20marketing%2C%26quot%3B%20Lenfestey%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20attorney%20relationship-based.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20law%20firms%20aren't%20required%20to%20disclose%20their%20use%20of%20service%20organizations%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20know%20how%20widespread%20the%20practice%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Pera%20and%20Lenfestey%20declined%20to%20list%20the%20firms%20they've%20worked%20with%20using%20the%20structure%2C%20citing%20confidentiality%20obligations%20to%20their%20clients%2C%20but%20said%20it's%20becoming%20more%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPera%20said%20he%20knows%20of%20one%20firm%20that%20used%20the%20structure%20as%20far%20back%20as%202006.%20In%20more%20recent%20years%2C%20more%20law%20firms%20and%20investors%20have%20become%20interested%20in%20using%20MSOs%2C%20Pera%20and%20Lenfestey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20many%20more%20that%20are%20in%20process%20right%20now%2C%20and%20some%20of%20them%20are%20quite%20large%2C%26quot%3B%20Pera%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20fairly%20large%20insurance%20defense%20firm%20in%20this%20country%20that's%20looking%20at%20doing%20this.%20There's%20a%20fairly%20large%20AmLaw-ranked%20law%20firm%20that's%20looking%20at%20this.%20So%20there's%20a%20non-trivial%20number%20of%20these%20that%20are%20going%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20who%20have%20built%20up%20their%20practices%2C%20and%20who%20want%20to%20cash%20out%2C%20can%20do%20so%20by%20effectively%20selling%20part%20of%20their%20firm%20to%20someone%20else%20to%20manage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20also%20help%20firms%20scale.%20Selling%20shares%20of%20an%20MSO%20could%20help%20finance%20lead%20generation%20or%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatalex%20Network%2C%20which%20launched%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20is%20using%20the%20MSO%20model%20to%20invest%20in%20law%20firms%20with%20a%20longer%20time%20horizon.%20While%20a%20private%20equity%20firm%20might%20want%20to%20stick%20with%20a%20law%20firm%20for%20a%20few%20years%20before%20selling%20its%20stake%2C%20Catalex%20Network%20says%20it%20aims%20to%20form%20long-term%20partnerships%20with%20law%20firms%20by%20helping%20them%20establish%20MSOs%2C%20buying%20substantial%20stakes%20in%20them%2C%20combining%20their%20back-offices%2C%20and%20giving%20the%20firms%20the%20resources%20to%20compete%20with%20Big%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatalex%20Network%20offers%20bread-and-butter%20services%20like%20IT%2C%20payroll%2C%20compliance%20management%2C%20and%20accounting.%20But%20also%20services%20that%20are%20more%20specific%20to%20the%20legal%20industry%2C%20like%20recruiting%20and%20sophisticated%20enterprise%20software%20that%20would%20be%20cost-prohibitive%20for%20smaller%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20kind%20of%20what%20big%20law%20resources%20are%20and%20I've%20seen%20what%20small%20law%20resources%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jeffrey%20Goldenhersh%2C%20a%20Catalex%20Network%20founding%20partner%2C%20who%20previously%20worked%20at%20the%20Big%20Law%20firm%20Skadden%20Arps%20before%20moving%20to%20a%20boutique%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Catalex%20Network%2C%20the%20MSO%20structure%20offers%20a%20way%20for%20the%20company%20to%20grow%20with%20law%20firms.%20The%20American%20Bar%20Association's%20rules%20meant%20to%20preserve%20attorney%20independence%2C%20such%20as%20limits%20on%20fee-sharing%20with%20non-lawyers%2C%20are%20a%20non-issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20Catalex%20Network%20handles%20the%20back%20office%2C%20the%20lawyers%20can%20do%20less%20managing%20and%20more%20lawyering%2C%20Goldenhersh%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20real%20consolidation%20going%20on%20at%20the%20top%20end%20of%20the%20legal%20market%20and%20some%20of%20these%20smaller%2C%20midsize%2C%20boutique-type%20firms%20are%20getting%20a%20little%20bit%20left%20behind%2C%26quot%3B%20Jesse%20Hamilton%2C%20another%20Catalex%20founding%20partner%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we're%20trying%20to%20help%20them%20catch%20up%20and%20be%20able%20to%20step%20into%20the%20ring%20with%20some%20of%20the%20larger%20firms%20that%20have%20consolidated%2C%20have%20the%20best%20technology%2C%20the%20best%20AI%2C%20the%20best%20back%20office%20staff%2C%20and%20have%20them%20be%20able%20to%20compete%20and%20stay%20relevant%20in%20the%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-firms-outside-investment-mso-private-equity-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751793721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6862eb1785e81483682d12b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-firms-outside-investment-mso-private-equity-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Legal%20ethics%20rules%20largely%20bar%20non-lawyers%20from%20owning%20law%20firms.%20MSOs%20off