0self-proclaimed%20extreme%20procrastinator%2C%20explains%20how%20the%20trait%20has%20been%20an%20asset.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Richard%20White%2C%20CEO%20of%20AI%20note-taking%20company%20Fathom.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20talks%20about%20procrastination%20as%20a%20personal%20failing.%20I%20disagree.%20I'm%20an%20extreme%20procrastinator%2C%20and%20I've%20been%20building%20successful%20companies%2C%20like%20UserVoice%20and%2C%20most%20recently%2C%20Fathom%2C%20for%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20one%20of%20my%20greatest%20assets%20as%20an%20entrepreneur.%20I%20see%20procrastination%20as%20ruthless%20prioritization%20in%20disguise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229cae6870-3e3d-4435-8a18-f44d3afde55e%5C%22%3EConsider%20procrastination%20as%20data%20collection%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProcrastination%20is%20a%20way%20to%20gather%20more%20information%20before%20making%20critical%20decisions.%20When%20I%20delay%20a%20choice%2C%20I'm%20not%20being%20lazy%3B%20I'm%20waiting%20for%20the%20optimal%20moment%20when%20I%20have%20enough%20data%20to%20make%20the%20right%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20college%2C%20I%20judged%20the%20size%20of%20a%20project%20and%20left%20it%20to%20the%20last%20achievable%20minute.%20I%20might%20have%20frustrated%20my%20peers%20or%20not%20gotten%20the%20most%20out%20of%20every%20seminar%2C%20but%20I'd%20do%20exactly%20what%20was%20needed%20and%20nothing%20more.%20Since%20then%2C%20I've%20learned%20to%20be%20more%20thoughtful%20about%20my%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20this%20philosophy%20to%20build%20Fathom%2C%20which%20now%20has%20an%20eight-figure%20valuation.%20We%20started%20building%20the%20company%20in%202020.%20Instead%20of%20rushing%20to%20market%20with%20whatever%20technology%20was%20available%2C%20we%20waited.%20We%20gathered%20data.%20We%20watched%20AI%20capabilities%20evolve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20prior%20to%20the%20rollout%20of%20GPT-4%20and%20Claude%202%2C%20Fathom%20would%20yield%20basic%20call%20summaries.%20When%20GPT-4%20was%20made%20available%2C%20we%20saw%20its%20capabilities%20and%20knew%20concerted%20investment%20on%20our%20side%20would%20yield%20massive%20gains.%20It%20was%20a%20foundation%20for%20our%20more%20advanced%20call%20summary%20features%2C%20and%20any%20earlier%20investment%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20as%20useful%20to%20our%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20principle%20applies%20to%20my%20personal%20life.%20I%20plan%20trips%20at%20the%20last%20minute%20because%20I%20want%20to%20see%20what%20opportunities%20emerge%2C%20what's%20actually%20happening%20in%20my%20life%2C%20and%20what%20I%20might%20miss%20out%20on%20if%20I%20commit%20too%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20work%20environments%20or%20even%20relationships%2C%20being%20a%20procrastinator%20can%20annoy%20people.%20However%2C%20the%20real%20and%20most%20common%20downside%20of%20procrastinating%20is%20underestimating%20the%20effort%20required%20and%20starting%20something%20too%20late%20to%20meet%20the%20deadline.%20As%20a%20CEO%2C%20I%20get%20to%20define%20the%20deadlines%20or%2C%20in%20our%20case%2C%20create%20a%20deadline-free%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228a515ed-dd22-4991-9e1f-c3b68a91fb4b%5C%22%3EUrgent%20matters%20to%20trump%20important%20matters%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20adopted%20an%20unfashionable%20approach%20for%20a%20CEO%3A%20urgent%20trumps%20important.%20This%20keeps%20our%20entire%20company%20moving%20forward%20without%20anyone%20waiting%20on%20me%20to%20make%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20means%20that%20sometimes%20important%20but%20non-urgent%20things%20languish.%20I%20tell%20my%20team%20that%20if%20something's%20truly%20important%2C%20they%20should%20keep%20tagging%20me%20until%20I%20respond.%20This%20creates%20a%20culture%20where%20people%20at%20all%20levels%20in%20the%20company%20can%20advocate%20for%20what%20matters%2C%20and%20truly%20important%20tasks%20don't%20get%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20developed%20what%20I%20call%20the%20%26quot%3BJenga%20model%26quot%3B%20for%20running%20my%20company.%20Like%20the%20game%2C%20when%20a%20piece%20looks%20too%20difficult%20or%20risky%20to%20move%2C%20I%20leave%20it%20and%20come%20back%20to%20it%20later.%20I%20can%20think%20about%20a%20problem%20and%20then%20put%20it%20back%20down%20without%20fear.%20Months%20later%2C%20I'll%20pick%20it%20up%20again%2C%20and%20suddenly%2C%20the%20answer%20falls%20right%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20prioritize%20problems%20that%20will%20get%20bigger%20with%20time%2C%20such%20as%20making%20an%20important%20product%20change%2C%20as%20well%20as%20problems%20where%20the%20solutions%20are%20low%20stakes%20or%20reversible.%20Higher-stakes%20decisions%20that%20are%20non-reversible%20should%20be%20deferred%20to%20gather%20data%20as%20long%20as%20possible%2C%20or%20broken%20out%20into%20lower-stakes%20decisions%20that%20help%20gather%20data%20to%20inform%20the%20larger%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20product%20development%2C%20we%20circulate%20ideas%20internally%20while%20waiting%20for%20technological%20improvements.%20We%20don't%20rush%20features%20to%20market.%20Instead%2C%20we%20wait%20for%20the%20AI%20to%20get%20better%2C%20watch%20for%20what%20could%20go%20wrong%2C%20and%20optimize%20our%20timing.%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20have%20ever%20missed%20out%20on%20an%20opportunity.%20The%20reality%20in%20startups%20is%20that%20few%20things%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bhard%26quot%3B%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImplementing%20a%20deadline-free%20environment%20at%20Fathom%20means%20there%20hasn't%20been%20much%20negative%20feedback%20on%20this%20model.%20My%20team%20understands%20what%20we're%20prioritizing%20versus%20what%20we're%20doing%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b9e6971-ffad-428c-adb0-7618c628c628%5C%22%3ECEOs%20need%20to%20play%20to%20their%20strengths%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20alongside%20great%20entrepreneurs%20over%20the%20years%20has%20taught%20me%20that%20you%20can't%20build%20something%20around%20yourself%20that%20doesn't%20play%20to%20your%20strengths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20strength%20isn't%20planning%20or%20rigid%20schedules.%20My%20strength%20is%20recognizing%20optimal%20timing%2C%20gathering%20information%2C%20and%20making%20high-impact%20decisions.%20I%20delegate%20open-ended%20goals%20to%20my%20teams%20rather%20than%20micromanaging%20tasks.%20I%20encourage%20people%20at%20every%20level%20to%20make%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20think%20efficiency%20means%20doing%20things%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%20I%20think%20efficiency%20means%20doing%20things%20at%20the%20right%20time.%20You%20might%20be%20wrong%20about%20when%20something%20is%20needed%20or%20the%20time%20cost%20of%20execution%2C%20but%20that's%20the%20risk%20you%20take%20using%20your%20best%20collective%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20mindset%20has%20served%20Fathom%20incredibly%20well.%20We're%20exploring%20ways%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20take%20better%20notes%2C%20reduce%20unnecessary%20meetings%2C%20and%20democratize%20information%20sharing%20within%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20time%20someone%20tells%20you%20that%20procrastination%20is%20holding%20you%20back%2C%20ask%20yourself%3A%20Are%20you%20really%20procrastinating%2C%20or%20are%20you%20waiting%20for%20better%20information%3F%20Are%20you%20being%20lazy%2C%20or%20are%20you%20being%20strategically%20patient%3F%20Sometimes%20the%20best%20thing%20you%20can%20do%20is%20put%20the%20problem%20down%20and%20come%20back%20to%20it%20when%20you%20can%20solve%20it%20easily%20and%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-company-fathom-ceo-procrastinator-why-its-asset-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751793061000%2C%22visual%22%