n%20'brand%20safety'%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Liam%20Brennan%2C%20a%20marketing%20consultant%20and%20former%20ad%20agency%20director.%20%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20it%20sound%20like%20a%20cop%20out%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20approach%20brands%20are%20taking.%20Before%20it%20was%20'block%2C%20block%2C%20block%2C'%20now%20it's%20more%20about%20where%20my%20brand%20%3Cem%3Eshould%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20appearing.%20It's%20a%20more%20positive%20approach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20actions%20have%20turned%20up%20the%20heat%20on%20brand%20safety%20practices%2C%20a%20broader%20backlash%20has%20been%20building%20for%20some%20time.%20Brand%20safety%20began%20as%20a%20seemingly%20innocuous%20practice%20of%20preventing%20brands%20from%20appearing%20next%20to%20the%20worst%20of%20the%20internet%2C%20such%20as%20violence%2C%20pornography%2C%20and%20illegal%20content.%20But%20it%20gradually%20expanded%2C%20with%20brands%20seeking%20to%20avoid%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20political%20issues%2C%20or%20platforms%20that%20supported%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-judiciary-committee-probe-garm-brand-safety-conservative-media-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvestigations%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvertisers-elon-musk-x-ad-boycott-lawsuit-dismiss-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elawsuits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lawmakers%20and%20other%20high-profile%20conservatives%20have%20argued%20that%20ad%20practitioners%2C%20brand%20safety%20tech%20vendors%2C%20and%20industry%20groups%20forced%20the%20brand%20safety%20pendulum%20to%20swing%20too%20far%20into%20partisan%20areas%2C%20unfairly%20depriving%20right-leaning%20outlets%20of%20ad%20dollars.%20Media%20companies%20on%20the%20left%20have%20said%20they%2C%20too%2C%20have%20been%20harmed%20by%20advertisers%20who%20deemed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvertising-on-hard-news-negative-articles-doesnt-hurt-brand-safety-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enews%20sites%20as%20unsafe%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20may%20have%20started%20as%20a%20good%20idea%20expanded%2C%20and%20then%20became%20too%20broad%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mark%20Penn%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20advertising%20holding%20company%20Stagwell.%20%26quot%3BConsequentially%2C%20it%20wasn't%20really%20about%20brand%20safety%20%E2%80%94%20it%20became%20almost%20brand%20censorship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257fde338-3a24-4b35-a4d4-c08a3f0fae93%5C%22%3EThe%20emergence%20of%20brand%20safety%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20practice%20of%20brand%20safety%20arose%20as%20advertisers%20shifted%20from%20analog%20media%20buying%20%E2%80%94%20placing%20deals%20directly%20with%20the%20TV%20stations%2C%20billboard%20owners%2C%20or%20newspaper%20proprietors%20they%20wished%20to%20buy%20space%20with%20%E2%80%94%20toward%20digital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20technology%2C%20advertisers%20could%20target%20their%20audiences%20across%20swaths%20of%20websites%2C%20social%20platforms%2C%20and%20apps%20with%20just%20a%20few%20clicks.%20However%2C%20this%20meant%20they%20had%20less%20visibility%20about%20the%20content%20their%20ads%20were%20likely%20to%20appear%20next%20to.%20Brand%20safety%20technology%20was%20created%20to%20give%20advertisers%20more%20control%20over%20the%20types%20of%20content%20they%20wanted%20to%20fund%20or%20avoid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublishers-advertisers-keyword-blocking-climate-crisis-news-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKeyword%20block%20lists%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20an%20early%20but%20somewhat%20blunt%20tool%2C%20helping%20advertisers%20avoid%20appearing%20in%20articles%20about%20grisly%20news%20topics%20like%20murders%20or%20natural%20disasters.%20However%2C%20marketers%20often%20didn't%20maintain%20good%20block%20list%20hygiene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Za