The%20report%20took%20aim%20at%20an%20initiative%20called%20the%20Global%20Alliance%20for%20Responsible%20Media%2C%20which%20developed%20brand%20safety%20frameworks%20and%20common%20definitions%20that%20advertisers%20and%20Big%20Tech%20platforms%20like%20Meta%20and%20YouTube%20could%20universally%20adopt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk's%20X%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-x-adds-more-advertisers-to-antitrust-lawsuit-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esued%20several%20major%20brands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20Mars%20and%20CVS%20Health%2C%20alleging%20their%20participation%20in%20GARM%20involved%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20withhold%20ad%20dollars%20from%20the%20platform%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter.%20The%20conservative%20video%20platform%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvertisers-hit-back-at-rumble-boycott-antitrust-lawsuit-filing-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERumble%20also%20sued%20GARM%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20some%20of%20its%20members%2C%20making%20similar%20claims%20in%20its%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fad-group-to-suspend-garm-initiative-following-elon-musk-lawsuit-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGARM%20shut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20shortly%20after%20X's%20suit%20was%20filed.%20Its%20parent%20organization%2C%20the%20World%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%2C%20denied%20wrongdoing%20but%20said%20GARM%20didn't%20have%20the%20resources%20to%20fight%20the%20legal%20action.%20In%20a%20May%20legal%20filing%20seeking%20to%20dismiss%20the%20X%20case%2C%20the%20defendants%20said%20the%20lawsuit%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20use%20the%20courts%20win%20back%20business%20X%20had%20%26quot%3Blost%20in%20the%20free%20market%20when%20it%20disrupted%20its%20own%20business%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvertisers-elon-musk-x-ad-boycott-lawsuit-dismiss-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ealienated%20many%20of%20its%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20next%20to%20an%20X%20logo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661512f316bde8d4ead6cc86%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk's%20X%20has%20sued%20several%20brands%2C%20alleging%20advertisers%20colluded%20to%20withhold%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20ad%20revenue%20from%20the%20platform.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20WFA%20said%20GARM%20provided%20tools%20to%20help%20advertisers%20better%20exercise%20their%20freedom%20to%20choose%20where%20to%20place%20their%20ads%20in%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20their%20brands%2C%20and%20that%20it%20was%20always%20voluntary%20and%20pro-competitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWFA%20will%20continue%20to%20fight%20these%20allegations%2C%20and%20we%20are%20confident%20that%20the%20US%20judicial%20system%20will%20find%20in%20our%20favor%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20GARM%20is%20no%20more%2C%20the%20lawsuits%20and%20the%20Judiciary%20Committee's%20investigation%20continue%2C%20and%20the%20FTC%20has%20joined%20the%20brand%20safety%20battle%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFerguson%2C%20the%20FTC%20chair%2C%20has%20said%20that%20maintaining%20a%20free%20ad%20market%20and%20free%20speech%20is%20a%20top%20priority%20and%20that%20he%20hopes%20other%20ad%20companies%20will%20adopt%20policies%20similar%20to%20those%20in%20the%20Omnicom-IPG%20consent%20decree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226363%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andrew%20Ferguson%20FTC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6866d5413d5881a51c1cb251%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224355%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20Ferguson%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%2C%20has%20taken%20a%20keen%20interest%20in%20the%20ad%20world%20since%20assuming%20the%20role%20in%20January.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20notice%20extends%20to%20other%20advertising%20vendors%20in%20the%20brand%20safety%20sphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20the%20FTC%20sent%20sweeping%20civil%20investigative%20demands%20to%20media%20watchdogs%20and%20rating%20firms%2C%20including%20Media%20Matters%20and%20Ad%20Fontes%20Media%2C%20seeking%20information%20about%20their%20brand%20safety%20practices.%20In%20one%20such%20letter%2C%20viewed%20by%20BI%2C%20the%20FTC%20sought%20documents%20related%20to%20relationships%20with%20GARM%2C%20the%20publicly%20traded%20ad%20verification%20firms%20Integral%20Ad%20Science%20and%20DoubleVerify%2C%20and%20other%20entities%20that%20track%20and%20characterize%20%26quot%3Bmisinformation%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bhate%20speech%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bfalse%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bdeceptive%26quot%3B%20content%2C%20and%20other%20similar%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20FTC's%20actions%20have%20made%20many%20in%20the%20ad%20industry%20nervous%2C%20some%20execs%20consider%20much%20of%20brand%20safety%20to%20be%2C%20as%20Stagwell's%20Penn%20puts%20it%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bfabricated%20issue.%26quot%3B%20Penn%20said%20there%20were%20only%20limited%20situations%20in%20which%20brands%20might%20really%20be%20negatively%20affected%20by%20where%20their%20ads%20appeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20the%20polling%20I've%20done%2C%20conservatives%20think%20that%20they%20were%20being%20censored%20and%20demonetized%2C%20and%20liberals%20think%20they%20were%20being%20censored%2C%20so%20nobody%20was%20particularly%20happy%20about%20what%20was%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Penn%20said.%20(Stagwell%20owns%20the%20public%20opinion%20and%20advisory%20firm%20The%20Harris%20Poll.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22054d7456-acb6-4642-a783-fff4a800e414%5C%22%3EWill%20the%20brand%20safety%20crackdown%20benefit%20news%20publishers%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExecs%20at%20The%20Daily%20Wire%20say%20the%20scrutiny%20on%20brand%20safety%20was%20warranted%20and%20has%20gotten%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20team%20is%20inside%20of%20the%20bigger%20agencies%2C%20having%20discussions%2C%20whereas%20the%20door%20was%20automatically%20shut%2012%20to%2016%20months%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20The%20Daily%20Wire's%20SVP%20of%20ad%20revenue%2C%20Christine%20Hoffmann.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20getting%20business%20from%20Fortune%20500%20companies%2C%20like%20Chevron%2C%20like%20Amazon%2C%20like%20Paramount%2C%20and%20that%20was%20business%20that%20was%20nonexistent%20to%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20conservative%20news%20outlets%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-advertisers-embrace-conservative-media-fox-news-daily-wire-rumble-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20Fox%20News%20and%20The%20National%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20also%20noticed%20a%20bump%20in%20advertising%20interest%20since%20Trump%20took%20office%20for%20the%20second%20time.%20Ad%20industry%20insiders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-advertisers-embrace-conservative-media-fox-news-daily-wire-rumble-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20reflected%20advertisers'%20realization%20that%20half%20of%20the%20country%20voted%20for%20Trump%2C%20but%20that%20it%20could%20also%20be%20a%20signal%20of%20advertisers%20hedging%20against%20political%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20notion%20that%20the%20crackdown%20on%20brand%20safety%20will%20provide%20a%20long-term%20bump%20to%20news%20publishers%20is%20untested%20and%2C%20for%20many%20industry%20insiders%2C%20feels%20unlikely.%20An%20executive%20from%20the%20media%20buying%20giant%20GroupM%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjudiciary.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fevo-subsites%2Frepublicans-judiciary.house.gov%2Ffiles%2Fevo-media-document%2FJuhl%2520Testimony.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etestified%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20House%20Judiciary%20Committee%20hearing%20last%20year%20that%20just%201.28%25%20of%20its%20clients'%20global%20ad%20budgets%20went%20toward%20news%20outlets.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Alphabet%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Amazon%20%E2%80%94%20with%20their%20superior%20scale%20and%20adtech%20%E2%80%94%20are%20set%20to%20take%20in%20more%20than%20half%20of%20global%20ad%20spending%20outside%20China%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warc.com%2Fcontent%2Ffeed%2Fai-propels-alphabet-amazon-and-meta-to-547-market-share-outside-of-china%2F10685%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatest%20forecast%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20World%20Advertising%20Research%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOmnicom%20has%20agreed%20to%20be%20audited%20to%20demonstrate%20its%20compliance%20with%20the%20FTC's%20proposed%20consent%20decree%2C%20which%20also%20includes%20an%20agreement%20not%20to%20create%20block%20lists%2C%20unless%20requested%20to%20do%20so%20by%20clients.%20The%20FTC's%20provisional%20agreement%20says%20Omnicom-IPG%20can't%20collude%20with%20other%20firms%20to%20steer%20client%20ad%20spend%20based%20on%20political%20ideologies%2C%20which%20might%20cause%20some%20advertisers%20to%20simply%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-ruling-on-ad-giants-merger-could-hurt-news-outlets-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopt%20to%20avoid%20news%20altogether%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20BI%20previously%20reported%2C%20some%20ad%20industry%20insiders%20and%20analysts%20think%20the%20government's%20crackdown%20on%20brand%20safety%20is%20an%20overreach%20that%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-ruling-on-ad-giants-merger-could-hurt-news-outlets-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehurt%20publishers%20of%20all%20kinds%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20further%20consolidating%20power%20with%20the%20tech%20giants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce7da7b0-9637-4565-a8c5-b1a2bbad4946%5C%22%3ENew%20tools%20could%20help%20brands%20avoid%20the%20censorship%20label%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20room%20for%20GARM%202.0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20in%20the%20ad%20industry%20tell%20BI%20they're%20hopeful%20that%20brand%20safety%20could%20enter%20an%20apolitical%20era%2C%20powered%20by%20tech%20rather%20than%20individual%20decisions%20over%20blunt%20filters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20view%20is%20that%20AI%20will%20bring%20greater%20nuance%20to%20brand%20safety%20%E2%80%94%20making%20it%20more%20effective%20for%20buyers%20and%20less%20restrictive%20for%20sellers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Kohl%2C%20cofounder%20of%20the%20performance%20marketing%20firm%20Symitri.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKohl%20said%20startups%20like%20Mobian%20are%20building%20models%20that%20assess%20context%2C%20user%20sentiment%2C%20and%20real-time%20ad%20performance%20to%20identify%20which%20media%20environments%20deliver%20and%20which%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElsewhere%2C%20Stagwell%20is%20creating%20what%20Penn%20describes%20as%20a%20politically%20neutral%20news%20marketplace%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20adtech%20company%20The%20Trade%20Desk%2C%20enabling%20advertisers%20to%20buy%20multiple%20news%20sites%20at%20once%2C%20according%20to%20demographics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20brand%20safety%20might%20become%20more%20tech-enabled%2C%20it%20seems%20unlikely%20there%20will%20be%20a%20GARM%202.0%20for%20some%20time%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20far%20too%20easy%20to%20become%20a%20target%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lisa%20Macpherson%2C%20a%20former%20marketing%20executive%20who%20now%20serves%20as%20the%20policy%20director%20of%20Public%20Knowledge%2C%20a%20tech%20policy%20consumer%20advocacy%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20ask%20the%20advertising%20agency%20group%20Dentsu.%20Late%20last%20year%2C%20Dentsu%20quickly%20exited%20its%20involvement%20with%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%20coalition%20that%20had%20intended%20to%20encourage%20ad%20investments%20in%20%26quot%3Bcredible%26quot%3B%20news.%20Days%20after%20the%20press%20release%20about%20the%20coalition%20was%20published%2C%20the%20House%20Judiciary%20Committee%20requested%20documents%20from%20the%20ad%20firm%2C%20having%20noticed%20similarities%20to%20GARM.%20In%20response%2C%20Dentsu%20said%20it%20had%20decided%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadtechradar.com%2F2024%2F10%2F28%2Fdentsu-and-614-group-initiative-halted-after-gop-concerns%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bnot%20to%20pursue%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20initiative%26quot%3B%20nor%20%26quot%3Bpursue%20any%20other%20effort%20with%20similar%20aims.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMacpherson%20said%20advertisers%20would%20continue%20to%20do%20what's%20necessary%20to%20protect%20their%20investments%20in%20their%20brands.%20Yet%2C%20as%20the%20threat%20of%20lawsuits%20and%20document%20demands%20related%20to%20GARM%20rumbles%20on%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcannes-lions-2025-recap-ai-sports-brand-safety-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20in%20the%20ad%20industry%20will%20likely%20avoid%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bbrand%20safety%26quot%3B%20in%20emails%20or%20marketing%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20may%20describe%20it%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20Macpherson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20be%20very%20careful%20to%20couch%20it%20in%20language%20that%20evokes%20their%20constitutional%20right%26quot%3B%20to%20send%20ad%20dollars%20or%20not%20spend%20money%20on%20certain%20media%20outlets%20based%20on%20the%20suitability%20for%20their%20individual%20brands%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZaneis%20of%20TAG%20said%20the%20recent%20government%20and%20legal%20scrutiny%20of%20brand%20safety%20practices%20might%20have%20been%20the%20jolt%20the%20industry%20needed%2C%20forcing%20marketers%20to%20pay%20closer%20attention%20to%20an%20issue%20that%20had%20gotten%20out%20of%20hand.%3C%